  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You try to wrench your target’s ether from their body. The target needs to make a basic saving throw based on your chosen save or take 3d4 spirit damage and lose a focus point. The target automatically critically succeeds if they have no focus points to drain.</p><p> </p><p>On a failure or critical failure, your target loses a focus point as you acquire a @UUID[Compendium.immortal-ardor.feats.Item.cN0RefdXwBD9KgoF]{mote of ether}. You can then choose to absorb it as hit points, recovering hit points equal to the amount of damage dealt or to absorb it as a focus point, granting you one focus point. Once a target fails or critically fails the saving throw, you cannot take their focus points and acquire a mote of ether from them again for 24 hours.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Heightened(+1)</strong>: Damage for this spell increases by 1d4.</p>"
    },
